I included the jqueryval-script into my view and after typing a wrong input for the first non-ajax-loaded textbox is working.

After adding a new box over the plus button the validation for the second ajax-loaded textbox is not working anymore.

[![Only validation for first textbox][2]][2]


Today I&#39;ve searched a lot for this problem. I&#39;ve had learned that it is necessary to tell the jquery validator after the ajax call, that there are new elements in the formular. I found three approaches:

```javascript
// initializes the validation on page load, can be called only once
$(&#39;#myform&#39;).validate();

// Validates a single element
$(&#39;#myelement&#39;).val();

// Tell jquery validator the new form (only for unobstrusive validator?)
$.validator.unobtrusive.parse(&#39;#myform&#39;);
```

The funny fact is, that the validation of the second textbox is shown after the next plus button ajax call:

[![Validation triggered after second ajax call][3]][3]

# Solution:

You have to remove the validator and after the deletion you&#39;re able to parse the formular again:

```csharp
var form = $(formSelector)
    .removeData(&quot;validator&quot;) /* added by the raw jquery.validate plugin */
    .removeData(&quot;unobtrusiveValidation&quot;);  /* added by the jquery unobtrusive plugin*/

$.validator.unobtrusive.parse(form);
```

Reference: [unobtrusive validation not working with dynamic content][4]


